  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" P Krishna Mohan Reddy versus The State of Andhra Pradesh pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_5_1221_1247','2025INSC725'); ><font size='4'> <strong>P KRISHNA MOHAN REDDY<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF ANDHRA PRADESH </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 1221</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 725</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010005872025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the statement of an accused u/s.161, Cr.P.C implicating co-accused can be looked into qua such co-accused at the stage of anticipatory bail or regular bail; whether the High Court exercised its discretion in a judicious manner while declining to the petitioners. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 &ndash; s.161 &ndash; Evidence Act, 1872 &ndash; ss.30, 17, 21, 24-29, 145 &ndash; High Court denied anticipatory bail to the Petitioners relying on the confessional statements made by co-accused persons during interrogation<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 16-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> SPECIAL LEAVE PETITION (CRIMINAL) No. 7532/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_5_1221_1247','2025INSC725','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','